events.originalText: The Egyptian revolution began with protests (protester pictured) on the "Day of Anger", eventually leading to the removal of President Hosni Mubarak after nearly 30 years of rule.
events.subtitle: 2011 Egyptian revolution
events.headline: Egyptian Revolution Leads to Removal of President Hosni Mubarak

events.originalText: Ethiopian Airlines Flight 409, en route to Addis Ababa, crashed into the Mediterranean Sea shortly after takeoff from Beirut, Lebanon, killing all 90 people on board.
events.subtitle: Ethiopian Airlines Flight 409
events.headline: Ethiopian Airlines Flight 409 Crashes, Killing 90 People

events.originalText: Three independent observing campaigns announced the discovery of OGLE-2005-BLG-390Lb., a super-Earth extrasolar planet 21,500 ±3,300 light years away from Earth near the center of the Milky Way.
events.subtitle: OGLE-2005-BLG-390Lb
events.headline: Super-Earth Planet Discovered 21,500 Light Years Away

events.originalText: Mexican professional wrestler Juana Barraza was arrested in conjunction with the serial killing of at least ten elderly women.
events.subtitle: Lucha libre
events.headline: Mexican Wrestler Juana Barraza Arrested for Serial Killings

events.originalText: Mars Exploration Rover Opportunity landed on Mars and rolled into Eagle crater, a small crater on the Meridiani Planum.
events.subtitle: Mars Exploration Rover
events.headline: Mars Exploration Rover Opportunity Lands on Mars

events.originalText: The Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam detonated a truck bomb at the sacred Buddhist  Temple of the Tooth in Kandy, killing 17.
events.subtitle: Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam
events.headline: Truck Bomb at Buddhist Temple in Kandy Kills 17

events.originalText: A team of Norwegian and American scientists launched a Black Brant XII sounding rocket, which was mistaken by Russian forces for a Trident missile.
events.subtitle: Black Brant (rocket)
events.headline: Rocket Launch Mistaken for Missile by Russian Forces

events.originalText: Pakistani national Mir Aimal Kansi shot five people outside the Central Intelligence Agency headquarters in Langley, Virginia, killing two.
events.subtitle: Mir Aimal Kansi
events.headline: Mir Aimal Kansi Shoots Five at CIA Headquarters, Killing Two

events.originalText: Avianca Flight 52 ran out of fuel on approach to John F. Kennedy International Airport and crashed into the village of Cove Neck, New York, resulting in the deaths of 73 people.
events.subtitle: Avianca Flight 052
events.headline: Avianca Flight 52 Crash Kills 73 in Cove Neck, New York

events.originalText: Idi Amin  seized power from Ugandan president Milton Obote in a coup d'état, beginning eight years of military rule.
events.subtitle: Idi Amin
events.headline: Idi Amin Seizes Power in Ugandan Coup

events.originalText: South Vietnamese junta leader Nguyễn Cao Kỳ fired his rival Nguyễn Hữu Có while the latter was overseas on a diplomatic visit.
events.subtitle: South Vietnam
events.headline: South Vietnamese Junta Leader Fires Rival Nguyễn Hữu Có

events.originalText: Representatives of the Chetnik movement began a four-day congress to organise political opposition to the Allied support of the communist-led Yugoslav Partisans in Yugoslavia.
events.subtitle: Chetniks
events.headline: Chetnik Movement Organises Political Opposition in Yugoslavia

events.originalText: Serving as a British armed merchant cruiser, Laurentic (pictured) was sunk by German naval mines off the northern coast of Ireland, resulting in 354 deaths.
events.subtitle: Armed merchantman
events.headline: British Ship Laurentic Sunk by German Mines, 354 Dead

events.originalText: American journalist Nellie Bly completed a circumnavigation of the globe by land and sea in a then-record 72 days.
events.subtitle: Nellie Bly
events.headline: Journalist Nellie Bly Circumnavigates Globe in Record Time

events.originalText: Thomas Hardy founded the London Corresponding Society to seek a "radical reform of parliament", later influencing the reform movements of early-19th-century England.
events.subtitle: Thomas Hardy (political reformer)
events.headline: Thomas Hardy Founds London Corresponding Society for Reform

events.originalText: English colonists from the Province of Carolina and their native allies began a series of raids against the largely peaceful population of Apalachee in Spanish Florida.
events.subtitle: Province of Carolina
events.headline: English Colonists Raid Apalachee Population in Spanish Florida

events.originalText: Anne Boleyn, already pregnant with the future Elizabeth I, secretly married Henry VIII of England in the second of his six marriages.
events.subtitle: Anne Boleyn
events.headline: Anne Boleyn Secretly Marries Henry VIII of England
